{"id": "food_FOOD00153", "name": "Radish (food medium)", "category": "food", "organism_scope": "food microbiome / general", "aerobic": true, "description": "Food-derived medium: metabolizable components of Radish (Raphanus sativus) [Vegetables] from FooDB, plus a standard M9 mineral base. Organic components use presence-based uptake bounds; FooDB content retained. Measured compounds with no BiGG exchange are listed under uncovered.", "namespace": "bigg", "provenance": {"source_type": "database", "citation": "FooDB v2020-04-07 (Wishart DS et al., foodb.ca). Content sources: DTU, DUKE, USDA.", "doi": "", "url": "https://foodb.ca/downloads", "notes": "Organic components mapped from FooDB compounds to BiGG via InChIKey/name. Mineral base added. Bounds presence-based; foodb_content retained. Unmapped measured compounds kept in uncovered (v2 completeness fix). IMPORTANT: composition values are taken from the archived FooDB 2020-04-07 CSV data release; FooDB's live food page no longer displays this bulk composition, so it will appear empty. Verify individual compounds via the per-component cross-reference links. Underlying content was aggregated by FooDB from USDA / DTU / Phenol Explorer.", "data_release": "FooDB 2020-04-07 CSV release (foodb.ca/downloads)", "food_record": "https://foodb.ca/foods/FOOD00153", "verification": "expert-curated (multi-source food composition; growth-relevant profile completed, FooDB noise removed)", "curation_date": "2026-07-17", "curation_sources": ["USDA FoodData Central FDC 169276 (Radishes, raw; SR Legacy) — sugars, amino acids, minerals, vitamins, fatty acids", "Agronomy 2025, 15(5):1216 doi:10.3390/agronomy15051216 — radish root sugars & oxalic acid (root-specific)", "Molecules 2016, 21(2):157 doi:10.3390/molecules21020157 — radish metabolite profiling (organic acids, TCA intermediates)", "Frontiers in Nutrition 2022 doi:10.3389/fnut.2022.889407 — radish taproot organic-acid metabolomics, root pH 5.49-6.04", "ResearchGate 8261995 — 'Raphanus sativus (Radish): Their Chemistry and Biology' (principal root organic acids)", "FooDB FOOD00153 (Radish) — starting compound list / osmolytes"], "curation_notes": "Raw radish root is a dilute, low-acid, sugar-dominated medium: the dominant carbon/energy sources are D-glucose (~1.05 g/100g) and D-fructose (~0.71 g/100g), with only trace sucrose. Organic-acid load is low (root pH ~5.5-6.0) and led by oxalic acid (~20 mg/100g); malic/citric/succinic/fumaric are present at trace levels. Protein and free amino acids are low, led by glutamate and aspartate. USDA free-sugar values were independently corroborated by Agronomy 2025 root-specific HPAEC data.", "curation_added": ["oxalic acid (dominant radish organic acid, quantified)", "malic acid, citric acid, succinic acid, fumaric acid, malonic acid (organic acids, present/trace)", "individual free sugars glucose/fructose/sucrose with real amounts (root-specific, not just total sugars)", "full amino-acid profile with amounts", "pantothenic acid, vitamin K1, choline (were partly implicit) with amounts"], "curation_removed": [{"name": "Cadmium", "reason": "non-nutritive toxic heavy metal / trace contaminant, not a growth nutrient"}, {"name": "Lead", "reason": "non-nutritive toxic heavy metal contaminant"}, {"name": "Mercury", "reason": "non-nutritive toxic heavy metal contaminant"}, {"name": "Aluminum", "reason": "non-nutritive contaminant element, not a required growth nutrient"}, {"name": "Silicon", "reason": "non-nutritive structural/trace element, not a microbial growth nutrient"}, {"name": "Rubidium", "reason": "non-nutritive trace element (K analogue), not a required nutrient"}, {"name": "Retinol", "reason": "preformed (animal-form) vitamin A; does not occur in a plant root (USDA vitamin A = 0). Plant provides only carotenoids"}, {"name": "Beta-Carotene", "reason": "negligible/absent in white radish ROOT (USDA vitamin A activity = 0 RAE); carotene occurs in radish leaves/tops, not the root matrix curated here"}, {"